cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper presents a fully data-driven approach for putting multiple dynamical systems into correspondence, which involves learning optimal control policies in new systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with control policies, which suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves constructing a latent space and using it to put different systems into correspondence, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
